 class="secondary" href=https://books.google.com/books?id=sDyqHO2LVosC&qtid=567e78cf&source=gbs_quotes_r&cad=5>Appears in 445 books from 1906-2008</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class=vertical_module_list_row><h3 class=about_title><a name="about_author_anchor"></a>About the author&nbsp;<span style="color:#666; font-weight:normal">(2004)</span></h3><div id=about_author class=about_content><div id=about_author_v><div class=textmodulecontent>Stanislao G. Pugliese is associate professor of modern European history at Hofstra University. He is the author of Carlo Rosselli: Socialist Heretic and Antifascist Exile and Desperate Inscriptions: Graffiti From the Nazi Prison in Rome, 1943-1944.
